cs.DB, cs.DC, cs.OS, cs.SY, cs.PL 

This paper is primarily focused on resource management in multi-tenant databases, which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). It also discusses the use of parallelism in these systems, which could potentially fall under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the use of operating system-level mechanisms for resource allocation (cs.OS) and the development of a framework (cs.PL) for simplifying and optimizing resource management. Finally, the paper discusses the use of production traces from real-world companies, which could potentially fall under systems and networking (cs.SY).
